title: Etui And Cover, 1780
description: Oval tubular etui. Sheath closure. Case (a) with retangular form, plain panels with bright-cut borders. At upper end a band of chased "s" scrolls and green gold leaves at top of each panel. Shallow flute in each panel. Bottom with engraved seal with coat of arms, unidentified. Cover (b) with similar decoration. Domed top with swirled rosette of green gold leaves.
